Lizz Astor. Lizz Astor has just won Best Film for her short film Tank, at the Rehoboth Beach International Film Festival. Here, she writes us about the incredible experience. This weekend I voyaged to Rehoboth Beach, Delaware, a place I had driven and casually breezed through many a summer on the way to the beach. My best friend and I drove three hours from my home in Baltimore to arrive at this beautiful, sleepy, tax free beach town to attend the Rehoboth Beach International Film Festival, which had decided, of the numerous entries, I was the winner of their student film award (and a glorious $1,000) check. I guess I should start from the beginning. Last May I completed post production on my first year film, â€œTankâ€, a narrative short that centers around divorce. My intention with the film was to create something hauntingâ€“a soft violence, and to highlight how devastating it is to see your mom cry. I screened the film to my class, and to the â€˜publicâ€™ on our last day of freshman year, and then posted it on Vimeo/ Facebook. I was amazed at the response, which was overwhelmingly positive. People reached out to me, telling me how much the film resonated with them and felt exactly that experience with their own parentsâ€™ divorce. As a person whose parents are happily together, and even occasionally cute, this meant a lot. I got an email about Rehoboth from SVA and figured why not. It was free and it couldnâ€™t hurt. I mailed a form in and waited for an email, which came 2 months later. I received many emails from Denise, the outreach coordinator, which ranged from asking if I had the rights to the music I had used (which I quickly acquired), to finally one that simply read: Congrats!! She asked if I was available to come to the festival to receive the award and I, wanting any reason to get out of the city and also not wanting to pass up an opportunity, agreed. RBFF was a five-day festival that was split between two locations. I was impressed by how many bigger independent films they were showingâ€“a lot of things now playing at IFC center, or Sunshine. Even more amazing is that this was the case considering the RBFF demographic, which was all people over 55. I arrived on Saturday evening with my best friend in tow. We spent a considerable amount of time exploring the desolate beach, and exchanging smiles with the locals, walking their golden doodles down the boardwalk. I received a call from Denise saying that Andrew (the award benefactor) was around and would like to meet me if I have the time. Of course I agreed. I arrive at the â€˜big tentâ€™ to meet Denise face to face and Andrew for the first time. Denise is short and slender with a pretty pink lipstick. Andrew has a kind face and wears a scarf. He tells me I donâ€™t look like a girl who wants to sit in a heated tent and chat, and heâ€™s right. We walk to what he believes is a dive bar, but turns out to be an upscale restaurant with live entertainment and a martini bar. We get something to drink. He very generously pays. Andrew is Andrew Fierberg, a big time producer who has done films like Secretary, Fur, Keane, and about 30 other titles. He tells me about escaping to Brooklyn at the dawn of gentrification, working as a plumber, and launching Maggie Gyllenhalâ€™s career. He tells me things I need to hear like: you donâ€™t want to be a technician, you want to be an artist, and that he hates HD TV. An hour later we leave and he gives me his card, which I learn later is a big deal. He tells me to email him because he would love to help and he thinks Iâ€™m smart and promising. I am flattered. And that Sunday night I fall asleep with a $1,000 check listening to the waves lap onto the beach.

12 Steps That Work: How to Jump Start a Car. 1. Park both cars nose to nose about a foot and a half apart. For automatics make sure the car is in park, for manual transmissions keep the car in neutral and set the parking brake.2. With both cars turned off and the key out of each ignition, pop the hoods and get down to business. If either carâ€™s battery is corroded or looks suspect, donâ€™t attempt to jump the car yourselfâ€”instead call a pro, the battery may need replacing. 3. Identify the positive and negative terminals on each battery. Along with a plus-sign, the positive terminal can be identified by red coloring; for the negative side look for a minus-sign and black coloring. 4. Now, Identify the positive and negative ends of your jumper cablesâ€”red for positive, black for negative. Make sure the metal ends donâ€™t touch one another throughout the process. Note: Different jumper cables have different markings. Our advice? Go for the most simple color-coded option. 5. Start by attaching the red/positive jumper cable to the dead batteryâ€™s positive terminal. 6. Attach the other end of the red/positive cable to the live batteryâ€™s positive terminal. 7. Now attach the black/negative end of the cable to the live batteryâ€™s negative terminal. 8. With the other end of the negative cable, attach it to a metal non-painted part of the car under the hood with the dead battery. Stay away from the battery itself and attach the cable to the engine blockâ€”unpainted bolts are a good go-to. Some cars have a jumping post for this purposeâ€”check your ownerâ€™s manual and be sure to avoid moving parts like belts or fans. 9. Now clear the area. 10. Start the engine of the car with the live battery. Let it run for a few minutes and lightly rev the engine. 11. Now, start the car with the dead battery. If she turns over, let her run for a few minutes. If she doesnâ€™t start the first time, give it another minute to two of rest with the good car running. If it still doesnâ€™t work, you may need to check your connections or call for a tow. 12. Once the dead car is running, disconnect the cables in the reverse order you put them on (i.e. negative connection on dead car, negative connection on good carâ€™s battery then positive cable from good carâ€™s battery and finally positive cable from bad carâ€™s battery). Always check the ownerâ€™s manual to see if your car requires a different process. How to Jump Start a Car (Popular Mechanics)

Tokyo Tower. Image sourced from yurijay@instagram While it bears striking similarities to a certain other tower in a certain French city, the Tokyo Tower is a distinctive icon of none other than, the city of Tokyo (hence the name). Both an observation tower, and a communication tower, the Tokyo Tower is the second tallest artificial structure in all of Japan and one of the most iconic tourist destinations in Tokyo. Built in 1958, and inspired by the Eiffel Tower, the Japanese are never to be outdone as the Tokyo Tower is a whole 13 meters taller than the original. And while spectacular night scenes make the towers look even more similar, the Tokyo Tower is a distinctive red and white colour. However, this is apparently for aviation safety reasons and not aesthetic reasons and the colour is apparently â€œinternational red orange.â€ï¿½ï¿½ Image sourced from shunyoshiko@instagram As a huge city person, as they call it, Iâ€™m very familiar with the concept of iconic buildings or structure in cities. In fact, theyâ€™re one of my favourite things about cities. Not so much having a whole forest of tall skyscrapers, but iconic constructions of welded steel and concrete that serve as a reminder that in the midst of the space-saving functionality that is the city, there can be beauty too.ï¿½ï¿½ Image sourced from anothersky0815@instagram While I have known about the Tokyo Tower since I first became interested in Japan, it really rose from tourist destination to must-go destination in my mental checklist after I watched the Japanese TV show Android-AI knows Love. Set in modern day Tokyo, it is a short, 10 episode cheesy romance drama with elements of action and sci-fi. Throughout the drama, the Tokyo Tower is always in the background whenever the characters are reminiscing about their romance history, and it becomes so symbolic of their love that at some point the male protagonist even suggests an engagement ring in the shape of the Tokyo Tower (dream ring for any girl female protagonist it did not make).ï¿½ï¿½

HHA Theme Challenge: Harmonious ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ how I reached 1.3m points IF YOU HAVENâ€™T COMPLETED ALL INTERIOR CHALLENGES, DO NOT START THE THEME CHALLENGE! I missed out on getting the gold model home bc I started my theme challenge before reaching the 300k point marker. According to this gamefaqs thread, once you start your theme challenge it overrides any interior prizes you still havenâ€™t won. So please be sure to have reached 300k before starting your theme challenge! You can start it at ANY time by talking to Lyle in Nookâ€™s Homes. click the pictures for prominent furniture sets/series, and room location First off, Iâ€™ve been told by a lot of people that itâ€™s way easier to accomplish this feat by picking the fairy-tale theme. But I swore to not have a mermaid exterior, and Iâ€™d already fallen in love with my Cabana/vacation room and the refurbished Exotic series. Plus, I happen to really love the Zen exteriors, so this all worked out! IMO itâ€™s best if you go with whatever theme you ultimately want your exteriors to fall under, as those are the hardest and most annoying to get. USING GUIDES I struggled my ass off trying to figure out which furniture sets were Harmonious. There are a lot of awesome websites out there (ac wikia, moridb, thonky), but PLEASE try to cross check information! Thonky had alpine listed under Harmonious, but when I put it in my back room, my score dropped from ~990k to ~500k. My advice (which requires patience) is to check your score, add A COUPLE of furniture items from a series/set in ONE room, and the next day check with Lyle to see if your score goes up or down. If it goes down, you know it doesnâ€™t fit your theme, If it goes up, then youâ€™re good to go. I wasted half a lifetime refurbishing the Alpine series only to not need it. Some series are also a mystery!! Since Lyle doesnâ€™t actually break down your points earned, I have NO CLUE if the Rococo or Cabin series count as Harmonious. As of right now, my score is ~1.3m. According to every guide I used, Rococo fell under Antique/Fairy-Tale and the Cabin series was Rustic. I donâ€™t think I would be capable of reaching that high of a score with TWO rooms not fitting the theme. My advice is to attain the Exotic series, Cabana series, and Zen/Zen Garden sets first. FURNITURE FILLERS So youâ€™ve completed your series and sets, but donâ€™t know what else to fill your room with? Bonsai are your best friend! And they help with your feng shui if you put the green ones on your southern-most walls (Jasmine bonsai should go to the left, and Maple bonsai should go to the right). All bonsai trees fall under the Harmonious theme, and they seem to mesh well with just about all the rooms. If you already have a cluster of favorite items (for me, I couldnâ€™t let go of my Dala horse or Skeleton Figurine), just check moridb to see what theme it falls under! I certainly didnâ€™t clear out EVERY single non-Harmonious item in my rooms, but it really does help in the long run to have as little as possible. After all, if 90% of your room falls under the theme, you get even more points. (For a room with the full 48 items, this means only 4-5 items can be non-Harmonious). YOU CAN CHANGE YOUR THEME AT ANY TIME If you really hate the direction your house is going, you can always change your theme by talking to Lyle. But ultimately, the house you design to reach 1.1m points does NOT have to be your dream house. I can tell yâ€™all right now I knew from day one that I was gonna scrap my zen room, but I put up with it bc I knew it was going to help me get the amount of points I needed. Donâ€™t change your theme bc you really hate ONE room. Just be patient, and know that once you get to 1.1m, you can scrap your entire house if thatâ€™s what your lil heart desires! Just have fun and experiment away! Towards the end of this challenge, I felt like it was such a chore, but it doesnâ€™t have to be that way. If you take the time to really explore your furniture options and pick a theme you really like, it will feel so rewarding.

Kitsis says, â€œIn the finale, weâ€™re also going to learn more about the Authorâ€™s past. Yes, [through] flashbacks.â€ Also, whoâ€™s to say that we arenâ€™t just all in one big storybook? 4. Someoneâ€™s death will set up next yearâ€™s big plot â€œWe will be telling you what next year is about in the final scene,â€ Kitsis says. â€œWhereas last year we saw Frozen, and the year before we were going to Neverland, this will be much more like Season 1 in that itâ€™s going to be a change in condition.â€ Co-creator Adam Horowitz adds, â€œThere is a death that precedes [the change in condition.]â€ 5. The Author may die Traditionally, The Author is only supposed to record events, not change them, but Isaac has proven to meddle quite a lot in peopleâ€™s fates, which is why the villains are so riled up with constantly being denied their happy endings. If Isaac makes huge changes to the Storybrooke crowd and then dies, this could set up the change in condition dilemma thatâ€™s been teased for next year. â€œCan the Authorship be passed on? I would say we actually answer that exact question in the finale,â€ Horowitz says. â€œWe show you how Isaac gets to be The Author.â€ 6. Zelena (Rebecca Mader) may die Like The Author, her death could cause problems, especially if sheâ€™s done something magical or set up a curse that affects everybody. Sadly, it would also eliminate the need to address the fact that sheâ€™s carrying Robin Hoodâ€™s baby, which Regina would probably be happy about. Good riddance, half sis! 7. Gold/Rumplestiltskin (Robert Carlyle) may die Hear us out. Although it would be easy for Onceto kill off someone that we donâ€™t know well or care about (such as The Author or Zelena), wouldnâ€™t it matter more if one of the core cast died? Goldâ€™s heart has been seriously damaged, and last we saw him, he was drained, sitting on the floor of his pawn shop. Also, Kitsis says that the Belle-Gold-Will love triangle â€œwill absolutely be ending. Weâ€™ll get a conclusion on that.â€ On one hand, that could mean that Goldâ€™s death will remove him from the triangle, but on the other hand, his death could be the catalyst that makes Belle (Emilie de Ravin) realize her feelings for him run much deeper than they do with Will (Michael Socha). What happens if the Dark One dies? We could find out! (Also, rarely does anyone die permanently on this show, so Gold could come back next year.) 8. Henry may become the next Author We know that Henry (Jared Gilmore) is going to step up his game in the finale. Finally! After all, as the Saviorâ€™s son and Goldâ€™s grandson, weâ€™ve been waiting for him to get pulled into some sort of grand heroics or show off some innate ability. But why would he become the Author? From the start, heâ€™s had an affinity for the original storybook and realized that the stories in it were true. Also, as weâ€™ve seen this year, heâ€™s been central to the success of Operation Mongoose and anything to do with those storybook pages. Check out this photo: Thatâ€™s a copy of Heroes and Villains, with what appears to be a vintage (1960s, perhaps?) cover. Just as a side note that Isaacâ€™s last name on the book is â€œHeller.â€ Hmm, could this be a hat tip to Joseph Heller, whose novel Catch-22 hit it big around the 1960s?Also, according to an episode description from ABC, â€œHenry discovers he has big shoes to fill as he steps up to save his family before the storyâ€™s final page is turned.â€ What size shoes does Isaac wear? We kid! Sort of. 9. Henry may die As with Gold, having Henry die would make the stakes really matter. If he steps up as Savior Jr., he could make the ultimate sacrifice, and this could cause ripples if heâ€™s also the new Author. And it will add some urgency going into the next season if everyone is working to undo this tragedy. Cara Menyembuhkan Kencing Nanah Secara Alami. Cara Menyembuhkan Kencing Nanah Secara Alami - Dalam menjalani kehidupan kita harus selalu selektif dan berhati-hati khususnya bagi mereka yang sudah dewasa dan melakukan hubungan intim. Dari pergaulan bebas tersebut akan menimbulkan berbagai jenis macam penyakit. Salah satunya adalah penyakit kencing nanah. Penyakit kencing nanah merupakan salah satu penyakit yang menyerang pada alat ï¿½ï¿½kelamin. Penyakit jenis ini tidak hanya menyerang kepada pria saja tetapi juga wanita. Memang bagi orang awam penyakit ini jarang terdengar karena memang penyakit ini lebih berpotensi terhadap mereka yang sudah berkeluarga. Penyakit ini disebabkan oleh bakteri jahat yaitu bakteri Neisseria gonohoea. Bakteri ini dapat menimbulkan kerusakan dan infeksi pada leher rahim, saluran kandung kemih, rectum tenggorokan dan bola mata. Penyakit kencing nanah ini termasuk penyakit yang menular. Penularan tersebut melaui beberapa macam cara baik itu dengan hubungan intim ataupun hal lainya. Dan perlu diperhatikan penyakit satu ini dapat menyebar keseluruh bagian tubuh melalui aliran darah. Oleh karena, penyakit satu ini merupakan penyakit yang cukup berbahaya. Gejala utama dari penyakit kencing nanah ini adalah keluarnya air nanah saat buang air kecil. Selain itu, gejala lain dari penyakit kencing nanah ini adalah air kencing berwarna kehijauaan, bertambahnya cairan dari vagina, terserang beberapa infeksi dibagian tubuh lalu susah untuk melakukan aktifitas sehari-hari. Bagi Anda yang merasakan penyakit tersebut jangan takut dan khawatir karena sekarang ini terdapat obat ampuh kencing nanah. Obat ampuh ini bukan obat biasa yang harus dengan harga mahal ataupun penggunaan teknologi canggih. Memang kita akui untuk jenis obat tersebut memilki khasiat yang cepat dan instant. Akan tetapi dibalik itu semua akan merasakan dampak yang cukup berbahaya. Berikut Sekilas Tentang Penyakit Kencing Nanah : Cara Mengatasi Kencing Nanah Pada Pria - Kencing nanah (Gonore) adalah penyakit menular seksual (PMS). Kencing nanah disebabkan oleh Neisseria gonorrhoea, bakteri yang dapat tumbuh dan berkembang dengan mudah pada saluran reproduksi yang hangat dan lembab, termasuk pada serviks (mulut rahim), uterus (rahim), dan tuba falopi (saluran telur) wanita, dan di uretra (saluran urin) wanita dan pria. Gonore menular melalui kontak dengan penis, vagina, atau anus. Tidak harus ada ejakulasi untuk terjadinya penularan atau terjangkitnya penyakit ini. kencing nanah juga dapat ditularkan ibu kepada anaknya selama kelahiran. Penyebab Penyakit Kencing Nanah : Hubungan Seksual secara Bebas Hubungan seksual yang dilakukan secara bebas merupakan faktor penyebab utama terinfeksinya penyakit ini. Hal ini karena hubungan seks yang dilakukan dengan cara berganti-ganti pasangan memungkinkan seseorang yang mengidap penyakit ini untuk meularkannya. Penularan penyakit kencing nanah akan berlanjut terus sebelum penderita berhenti melakukan hubungan seks bebas ataupun sembuh total. Aktivitas Seksual yang Tidak Sehat Hubungan seks bebas juga merupakan salah satu bagian dari aktivitas seksual yang tidak sehat, namun selain itu ada beberapa faktor lain yang juga ikut bepengaruh dalam penularan penyakit ini. Aktivitas seks lainnya diantaranya yaitu oral seks, anal seks, seks non penetratif dan aktivitas seksual lainnya. Ibu yang Melahirkan Seorang ibu yang mengidap penyakit ini dapat menularkan penyakit tersebut kepada Anaknya apabila melahirkan secara normal atau melalui vagina. Kebersihan organ Intim Kebersihan organ intim merupakan faktor kesehatan organ tersebut. Apabila organ tersebut tidak bersih, maka kemungkinan terkena berbagai penyakitpun sangat besar. Termasuk penyakit kencing nanah. Maka dari itu sangatlah perlu kita menjaga kebersihan organ intim. Kebersihan Pakaian Pakaian merupakan pelindung atau penutup tubuh yang digunakan sehari-hari oleh kita. Setiap pakaian yang kita kenakan haruslah bersih agar tubuh kita tidak mudah terkena penyakit termasuk kencing nanah, karena bakteri atau virus penyebab penyakit selalu ada di tempat-tempat yang kotor. Celana dalam merupakan pakaian yang harus selalu terjaga kebersihannya, dan peggunaannyapun harus sering diganti dengan yang bersih secara teratur. Karena jika tidak, pakaian tersebut dapat menjadi sarang berkumpulnya bakteri-bakteri atau virus penyebab penyakit. Kebersihan Linkungan Lingkungan merupakan tempat kita tinggal, termasuk rumah dan daerah tempat tinggal sekitar. Jika lingkungan tersebut tidak bersih atau sehat maka berbagai penyakit akan mudah datang dan menyerang. Maka dari itu sangatlah penting untuk selalu merawat dan menjaga kebersihan dan kesehatan lingkungan. Penyebab kencing nanah diatas merupakan faktor penyebab kencing nanah yang saya ketahui, maka dari itu sangatlah wajar jika ada penyebab kencing nanah lainnya yang tidak saya tuliskan dalam artikel ini. Untuk kejelasannya, saya sarankan Anda untuk menanyakan kepada dokter secara langsung. Gejala Penyakit Kencing Nanah : Pada pria, gejala awal penyakit kencing nanah biasanya timbul dalam waktu 2-7 hari setelah terinfeksi. Gejalanya berawal dengan rasa tidak nyaman pada uretra dan beberapa jam kemudian diikuti oleh nyeri ketika buang air kecil serta keluarnya nanah dari penis. Sedangkan pada wanita, gejala awal biasanya timbul waktu 7-21 hari setelah terinfeksi. Penderita seringkali tidak merasakan gejala selama beberapa minggu atau bulan, dan diketahui menderita penyakit tersebut hanya setelah pasangan hubungan seksualnya tertular. Jika penyakit kencing nanah menimbulkan gejala, biasanya bersifat ringan dan mendadak hilang dengan sendirinya. Tetapi beberapa penderita menunjukkan gejala yang berat, seperti desakan untuk berkemih, nyeri ketika berkemih, keluarnya cairan dari vagina, dan demam. Infeksi dapat menyerang leher rahim, rahim, saluran telur, indung telur, uretra, dan rektum serta menyebabkan nyeri pinggul yang dalam ketika berhubungan seksual. Wanita dan pria homoseksual yang melakukan hubungan seks melalui anus (anal sex) dapat menderita gonore pada rektumnya. Biasanya penderita kencing nanah akan merasakan tidak nyaman di sekitar anusnya dan dari rektumnya keluar cairan. Daerah di sekitar anus tampak merah dan kasar, serta tinjanya terbungkus oleh lendir dan nanah. Hubungan seksual melalui mulut (oral sex) dengan seseorang penderita gonore biasanya akan menyebabkan gonore pada tenggorokan (faringitis gonokokal). Umumnya infeksi tersebut tidak menimbulkan gejalam namun kadang-kadang menyebabkan nyeri tenggorokan dan gangguan untuk menelan. Jika cairan yang terinfeksi mengenai mata, maka bisa menyebabkan terjadinya infeksi mata luar (konjungtivitis gonore). Bayi yang baru lahir juga bisa terinfeksi gonore dari ibunya selama proses persalinan sehingga terjadi pembengkakan pada kedua kelopak matanya dan dari matanya keluar nanah. Jika infeksi itu tidak diobati, maka akan menimbulkan kebutaan. Full Frontal Knittery Back, again, heyyyy, hello! Doing some swatching for a steampunk shawl, see above. The yarn: Jaggerspun Zephyr, 50% Merino wool & 50% Tussah in Suede. Itâ€™s a subtle dun-tan color and the silk gives it the vaguest frisson of a metallic sheen. Itâ€™s my favorite lace weight yarn and I want to eat it with a spoon, even colors I donâ€™t like, even though itâ€™s 50% merin-ugh wool. It jumps through every hoop Iâ€™ve ever put it through, drapes like a narcoleptic snake and shines like a good deed in a evil world. *Happy, satisfied smile and sigh* Look at that glorious bastard. Love it. Tennyrate, Iâ€™m swatching it on 0â€™s, 1â€™s & even 2â€™s. I am a very loose knitter and usually choke up pretty hard on my gauge. I can, and happily do put Lion Brand Fishermanâ€™s Wool on 2â€™s. Yes, really. I want this shawl to sing, sing like a diva, so needs must I find the gauge thatâ€™ll be best for the lace, twisted, traveling and cable stitches I intend on putting in it. All the stitches, baby. All of them! *maniacal laugh* Iâ€™ve got 500 yards to swatch with & 1000 yards for the actual tester shawl. Details: I started with a long tail cast on at first and got through the 0â€™s section before my inner knitter started clearing her throat pointedly & fidgeting that the cast on looked kinda choked. After sighing at myself for getting in my own way yet again, I yarded the first part of the swatch out and started again with a knit cast on. Look at it. So sexy. My lace section is 40 stitches, with a four stitch garter selvedge front and back, slipping the first stitch of every row purlwise. The actual lace repeat is two rows, a multiple of 2: ROW 1: *YO, K2togtbl; rep from * to end. ROW 2: *K2tog, YO; rep from * to end. When one remembers to use oneâ€™s row counter, it comes out to a lovely, open, simple netting. I only do twelve rows, which is more than enough for me, in my opinion, to get a feel for what the stitch was going to do. I did the 0â€™s section on metal straights YET AGAIN, after the swatch decided to eat shit and take a screaming noser off the needles during the 2â€™s lace section at a local coffee joint. My own fault for using circular needles under 24â€ for a flat piece of work. I knew full fucking well itâ€™d bite me on my copious tuchis and it sure as shit did. The 1â€™s section was done on square metal straight 1â€™s, which I love. Iâ€™m pretty sure the tester and final shawl will be done on 1â€™s, but Iâ€™m continuing on with the 2â€™s sections, because a) aforementioned yarnsplosion, and b) my gauge has changed significantly over the last year & I donâ€™t want to be 20 rows into the tester and change my tiny little mind again. For the solid pattern of the swatch, I like to do a simple set of reverse stockinette, a 4 stitch cable between it on either end with a section of stockinette in the middle. Usually about 20-24 rows to show how the cables are gonna act, easy like Sunday morning. In personal knitting; Iâ€™m making myself an earphone pouch in some leftover sock yarn in which I made my mom mittens. Itâ€™s several different shades of yellow *delicate shudder* which I personally canâ€™t stand. But itâ€™s an easy color to see, and losing my earphones drives me nearly as nuts as misplacing my friggin debit card. I saw a pattern floating around here on tumblr that looked easy enough to reverse engineer, and a quick knit. I need to buckle down and work on that outline for knitting world domination, Iâ€™ll probably poke at it later today, or start it at work tomorrow night. I do so like making outlines and lists, them break things into little bits so I donâ€™t get all panicky and wind up doing nothing I intended to & hiding in bed in a welter of self loathing and frustration. All right, knitters. See you next time with more random updates, hood design ideas and silliness.

Full Frontal Knittery Back, again, heyyyy, hello! Doing some swatching for a steampunk shawl, see above. The yarn: Jaggerspun Zephyr, 50% Merino wool & 50% Tussah in Suede. I want this shawl to sing, sing like a diva, so needs must I find the gauge thatâ€™ll be best for the lace, twisted, traveling and cable stitches I intend on putting in it. All the stitches, baby. All of them! *maniacal laugh* Iâ€™ve got 500 yards to swatch with & 1000 yards for the actual tester shawl. Details: I started with a long tail cast on at first and got through the 0â€™s section before my inner knitter started clearing her throat pointedly & fidgeting that the cast on looked kinda choked. After sighing at myself for getting in my own way yet again, I yarded the first part of the swatch out and started again with a knit cast on. Look at it. So sexy. My lace section is 40 stitches, with a four stitch garter selvedge front and back, slipping the first stitch of every row purlwise. The actual lace repeat is two rows, a multiple of 2: ROW 1: *YO, K2togtbl; rep from * to end. ROW 2: *K2tog, YO; rep from * to end. When one remembers to use oneâ€™s row counter, it comes out to a lovely, open, simple netting. I only do twelve rows, which is more than enough for me, in my opinion, to get a feel for what the stitch was going to do. I did the 0â€™s section on metal straights YET AGAIN, after the swatch decided to eat shit and take a screaming noser off the needles during the 2â€™s lace section at a local coffee joint. My own fault for using circular needles under 24â€ for a flat piece of work. I knew full fucking well itâ€™d bite me on my copious tuchis and it sure as shit did. The 1â€™s section was done on square metal straight 1â€™s, which I love. Iâ€™m pretty sure the tester and final shawl will be done on 1â€™s, but Iâ€™m continuing on with the 2â€™s sections, because a) aforementioned yarnsplosion, and b) my gauge has changed significantly over the last year & I donâ€™t want to be 20 rows into the tester and change my tiny little mind again. For the solid pattern of the swatch, I like to do a simple set of reverse stockinette, a 4 stitch cable between it on either end with a section of stockinette in the middle. Usually about 20-24 rows to show how the cables are gonna act, easy like Sunday morning. In personal knitting; Iâ€™m making myself an earphone pouch in some leftover sock yarn in which I made my mom mittens. Itâ€™s several different shades of yellow *delicate shudder* which I personally canâ€™t stand. But itâ€™s an easy color to see, and losing my earphones drives me nearly as nuts as misplacing my friggin debit card. I saw a pattern floating around here on tumblr that looked easy enough to reverse engineer, and a quick knit. I need to buckle down and work on that outline for knitting world domination, Iâ€™ll probably poke at it later today, or start it at work tomorrow night. I do so like making outlines and lists, them break things into little bits so I donâ€™t get all panicky and wind up doing nothing I intended to & hiding in bed in a welter of self loathing and frustration. Month of Saiyuki Day 4. English What is your favorite episode in the Animes (Gensomadem/Reload/Gunlock)? Hmnnâ€¦I have quite a few favorite episodes and arcs and for me itâ€™s difficult to really settle on just one. I quite do enjoy the filler episodes as they can give you an extended insight into the world of Saiyuki and our boys, the things that donâ€™t get covered by the manga alone. But picking one is a must soâ€¦ While it sounds cliche, I will say my top favorite episode has to be Reload #7 â€œLittle Partnerâ€ a.k.a. â€œthe kitten episodeâ€. Itâ€™s cute, itâ€™s funny as hell watching Sanzo with his allergy problems, but I like to look into the episode much deeper than that. Take all that away and what I think is the real purpose of the episode is to show fans Sanzo is not a cold hearted bastard like so many people get stuck in believing! (Is it really that hard to see past the front he puts on?). And probably too much of a stretch for some, but oh well, seeing as the kitten is a female perhaps it somewhat hints how Sanzo might treat womenâ€¦as in heâ€™s pretty clueless when dealing with women (Minekura has stated through Gojyoâ€™s words in an interview this is true). Sanzo is as much of hard-ass due to his personality as well as because of the things in life that have hardened him. One of his weaknesses is that when he does care, he cares A LOT. My personal conclusion leads me to believe that for Sanzo it is very surprising that anyone wants to get close to him (generally speaking) despite him being up front about keeping himself distanced. His natural reaction to more directly continue to drive them off, but eventually if the other party keeps trying he will warm up to them. The man is hard-headed and stubborn by nature so â€œgiving inâ€ is not an easy thing but it does happen. This is what happens in this episode, as Sanzo is surprised the kitty brings him matches for his cigarette (thatâ€™s one heck of a smart kitty!) . He doesnâ€™t want her getting close but you can tell heâ€™s starting to accept the kitty does care for him whether he likes it or not. We also get proof why Sanzo should ~never~ be allowed in a kitchenâ€¦.Anyways, milk over boils, kitty jumps into the safety of Sanzoâ€™s arms and despite all that they take a nap together (all together nowâ€¦â€awwwwâ€). Isnâ€™t she the just happiest kitty when next to the grumpy blonde? xD; But the big kicker comes when youkai get into the room to attack Sanzo, the kitty jumps to defend him and gets seriously injured. Sound familiar? The only thing that could possibly have struck Sanzo in a milli-second is this was exactly how his Master Komyou Sanzo defended him, got struck down and killed. Thatâ€™s why Sanzo is telling the kitty to hang on and when it seems sheâ€™s not gonna make it, Sanzo looses it. A small incident that reminds him in seconds of one of the most marking events in his life, of course itâ€™s â€œunforgivableâ€ to let it repeat and thatâ€™s why heâ€™s beyond pissed that in fact he goes into his â€œcold heartedâ€ mode when he is absolutely merciless. Iâ€™m not saying heâ€™s never â€œnotâ€ cold hearted but moments like these that push him over the edge. Iâ€™m reminded of the desert chapter heâ€™s tortures the cross-dressing youkai and forgets â€œwhat is like to beâ€ himself. Good thing for his companions being there to snap him out of those moments. As the episode draws to a close and theyâ€™re outside the vet hospital, who of allï¿½ï¿½ but of all people should happen be holding the basket with the kitty? SANZO OF COURSE! He certainly doesnâ€™t seem quite like his usual selfâ€“ hell heâ€™s worriedâ€¦just LOOK at his face! â€œAnd thatâ€™s why I said we shouldnâ€™t bring her alongâ€¦â€ he says. Itâ€™s a dangerous journey. Asides the four of them that absolutely have to go on this journey, bringing along anyone else would be quite difficult and dangerous. Not being able to theoretically protect someone you care about so much itâ€™s quite a difficult emotion to deal with. So a lot of conflicting emotions hidden in this episode. But in the end, where Sanzo felt guilty that the kitty had gotten hurt, he can feel relief because she calls out (or rather meows out) to him and smiles. She still likes him the most and is happy to haveï¿½ï¿½â€œmet himâ€ before going back to her owner. That surprises our Sanzo but he accepts it some can actually like him, which is why we get this small but nonetheless, a warm smile. So why does Sanzo not like cats? Because he probably would end up liking them anywaysâ€¦or caring whether he likes it or not.

preprotext: You are kind of unique in that you actively try to include a diverse cast of characters in your project. Why do you think most developers do not? -IK. Including a diverse cast is scary. It goes against the proven model. Big developers have proven that they can slap in Angry White Man or some large-chested women in a catsuit and sell millions of copies. Will gamers play as a heavier, middle-aged woman? Will gamers play as a black woman? These these are unknowns and unknowns are scary. The audience for games has diversified in recent years, but no one is really sure if this new audience has the buying power to carry a game. And no one is really sure how much of theï¿½ï¿½â€œtraditionalâ€ audience youâ€™ll lose with atypical lead characters. So thereâ€™s a lot of financial risk involved in trying to make a diverse game. Trying to be diverse also opens you up to criticism both for being too diverse and for not being diverse enough. Literally, in my Tumblr inbox, I have a post telling me Aberford sucks because it has too many minority characters, and two messages later someone tells me that Aberford sucks because I didnâ€™t include enough minority characters. Neither criticism has anything to do with the gameplay or the story. Theyâ€™re simply a side effect of trying to be inclusive and that scares developers. Weâ€™re just trying to make a small game with our own money plus about half a million dollars in funding. I canâ€™t imagine the risk that a company spending $100 million perceives when asked to be different. Diversifying a game also opens you up to a criticism about the quality of your diversification (a problem that doesnâ€™t exist if you stick with the proven model). People want to be represented in games, but they donâ€™t want to be misrepresented or portrayed in a way that they feel is negative. Thereâ€™s extra pressure in creating underrepresented characters, because theyâ€™re often viewed as a statement on the group at large. Any flaw or weakness (or lapse is writing quality) is viewed as a criticism of the group that character represents. Look at Black Widow in Age of Ultron. Is it possible that years of guilt and psychological trauma and showing pretend feelings instead of real ones, combined with seeing her best friendâ€™s beautiful children (that sheâ€™ll never have) and Mark Ruffaloâ€™s naked body (that she really wanted), make Natasha get all weird about her inability to have children? Probably. It was clumsy, but it wasnâ€™t absurd. It was a story that, with time to flesh it out, could have really worked for that character. However, because sheâ€™s the only woman on the team, her story has to stand for all women. Her stories have to fit a certain expectation, and if they donâ€™t, they end up alienating the very group they were supposed to connect with. If Nerd God and long-standing feminist Joss Whedon can get intensely flamed over a misstep, what hope to we sorry excuses for writers have? Plus, it takes a lot of work. Writing an angry white male is easy because the precedents are many and the expectations are low. Writing real female characters takes effort. Writing characters of color takes effort. Writing trans gender characters takes effort. And it opens you up to the risk of being a commercial or critical failure for reasons that have nothing to do with the actual quality of the game youâ€™ve made. So you really have to want to do it, and you have to really have the financial and creative freedom to do it, and thereâ€™s not a lot of devs that fit that bill. If weâ€™re not successful in our Kickstarter, we wonâ€™t fit that bill either.ï¿½ï¿½ TLDR: diversifying games carries a high financial risk and only really rewards you with the satisfaction of doing the right thing, which banks do not accept as payment. And if you mess it up: PAINFUL, AGONIZING FAILURE! (Shown below) So, if you want to see gaming get more diverse, try and support developers who are making the effort. Help them understand what to do (like you all have done for us) and be patient with their limitations. Keep pushing, obviously, but remember that itâ€™s an industry learning something new. Help them help you.

May 21st - May 28th. May 21st: Westminster Abbey! Our first official field trip of the semester abroad was to Westminster Abbey, which is absolutely beautiful, and remains in prime condition despite having been constructed in the 13th and 14th centuries. My favorite part was the Tomb of the Unknown Warrior, however there is no photography allowed in the Abbey, so I could not take any photos inside to share. An exterior view of Westminster Abbey. The open are walkway in the Abbey. The Abbeyâ€™s courtyard. A beautiful door. May 22nd: Day off! We had the day off for Friday the 22nd because we do not have class on Fridays to allow for longer field trips, however since it was our first full weekend we didnâ€™t have anything planned so it was a day to relax. May 23rd, 24th, 25th: More days off! Food shopping, cooking, running through parks and hanging out at the Crofton! May 26th: Magna Carta After class we took a field trip to the British Library to see an exhibit on the Magna Carta. I thought it was going to be this large and ornate document, however it was actually small and plain. May 27th: Kitchen duty and Jack the Ripper! After classes on the 27th half of our peer groups took a Jack the Ripper tour in Whitechapel, London where the murders originally took place. The area now has a grungy feel and is littered with graffiti - my badï¿½ï¿½â€œstreet artâ€. Sadly, the tour had very little to do with Jack the Ripper aside from very basic facts, which was a huge disappointment for me, although other students enjoyed the area. I on the other hand, will not be trading in Kensington any time soon. May 28th: Classes and Gelato Another easy day of classes, hanging at the Crofton and a short walk down to South Kensington for gelato and milkshakes. Tomorrow we are off to Bath and Stonehenge!

Here we shall count down her top 5 designers, and find out who the favourite of Ms Jolie. No. 5) BCBG Max Azria. The Frenchï¿½ï¿½fashionï¿½ï¿½house, which uses the mantra â€œbon chic, bon genreâ€ translating to â€œgood style, good attitudeâ€, has also dressed Jennifer Lopez, Catherine Zeta-Jones and Kate Winslet. Possible the most famous of Max Azriaâ€™s gowns that Jolie has donned was in 2008. At the premiere for â€œKung Fu Pandaâ€ in Cannes, whilst heavily pregnant with twins, Jolie wore a light moss floor-length gown. The low cut dress, from the Atelier collection, that featured light pleats contrasted beautifully with the red carpet and the â€œSaltâ€ actressâ€™ chocolate locks. www.bcbg.com No. 4) Next up is Ellie Saab, a personal favourite of mine. The designer, who hails from Beirut is famous for creating the most glamorous gowns that money can buy. A favourite with international royalty such as Queen Rania of Jordan and Princess Claire of Luxembourg, Jolie has worn Saabâ€™s designs on multiple occasions. At the 17thï¿½ï¿½Sarajevo Film Festival Jolie wore a stunning orange gown, with thigh-high slit, lose draped shape and ï¿½ï¿½ length sleeves was the epitome of glamour. www.eliesaab.com No. 3) Another designer that Angelina Jolie adores is Saint Laurent, formerly known as Yves Saint Laurent. At the BAFTAâ€™s last year, Ms. Jolie along with her significant other, wore a classic Saint Laurent Tuxedo, with untied bow tie for an added detail. www.ysl.com/gb No.2) Just missing the top spot is British powerhouse Ralph & Russo. Krush Bars: Peanut Butter Chocolate Crunch. Hello everybody! One of my colourful breakfasts is featuring a review again today - that protein bar at the bottom. A Krush Peanut Butter Chocolate Crunch bar. Iâ€™ve also tried the Birthday Cake variety, which also now has its own review. Exam season is kicking off fully on Monday, so I was certain I wanted to get at least one more review out before Iâ€™m enslaved to solely schoolwork. The first week is definitely the worst, but exams are obviously a huge part of my life and future so will most likely have the blog slightly on the backburner while I get those out the way - but afterwards, Iâ€™ll be kicking into motion big time! For now, though, enjoy this review! First of all, weâ€™ll talk about packaging, as we always do. Fairly plain and in a cellophane wrapper with a paper sticker on the front, you can see through just about at the sides. Itâ€™s nowhere near as graphics heavy as some protein bars - but itâ€™s simple, and gets the message across. As for out of the packaging, you can clearly notice how the flavours seem to have beenï¿½ï¿½â€˜foldedâ€™ together, with the peanuts, nut butter and chocolate. Itâ€™s soft too, but still on the firm side - definitely not mushy. As for taste - woah! I have to say Iâ€™m really impressed with this bar. It was smooth, with a distinct peanutty flavour but also chocolate and peanut chunks that were scattered throughout, giving it an interesting and varied texture.ï¿½ï¿½ The cocoa was noticeable too and very enjoyable - not bitter at all, the bar almost tasted similar to a peanut butter cup with more emphasis on the peanut. It also had those delicious morsels of chocolate chips in it as well. I have to say, overall, I really enjoyed this bar. It wasnâ€™t too sweet, yet it really satisfied me - it was a great, soft bar with those extra bits of texture that made it all the nicer. I didnâ€™t microwave it, but I didnâ€™t feel I needed to.ï¿½ï¿½ One interesting thing about these bars is how they only have a 2 month shelf life (extended slightly in the fridge, and up to 6 months in the freezer). This could be a problem if you tend to have a large stash of bars, but itâ€™s probably why theyâ€™re so soft and delicious. As for my overall verdict; Rating: 9/10 Absolutely delicious taste - one of the best tasting protein bars I think Iâ€™ve ever had. A small company in comparison to others, but one that definitely has something unique and tasty that makes it a worthy competitor. Nutrition: Higher macros than some other bars - but really, really good.

Catatan Perjalanan Gn.Papandayan, Mountaineering Kedua. Sorenya gue, #1 dan #3 ke posko STAPALA (mapalanya STAN) dulu buat minjem peralatan-peralatan kita yang masih belum lengkap. Abis itu, kita packing di kosan #1. Nyicil tidur bentar, biar besoknya seger lagi. Soalnya kita emang udah rencana naik pagi-pagi banget biar pulangnya gak kemaleman. Tektok (gak ngecamp, 1 hari naik-turun) lagi ceritanya. Petualangan kali ini dimulai di malam hari. Gue sekeluarga berangkat dari kosan kakak di Bintaro tepat jam 10 malam. Berenti bentar di kios martabak dan alfa mart buat beli logistik. Jam 5 kurang,kita udah nyampe Garut. Kita berenti di SPBU buat isi bensin+solat subuh dulu sebelum ngelanjutin lagi perjalanan ke kaki gunung. Jam 7 kurang, kita udah di daerah Cisurupan menuju kaki gunung. Gue ngeliat pendaki2 pada rame gitu disitu. Mungkin faktor di daerah ini ada 2 gunung, Cikurai sama Papandayan. Udah gitu, di kanan-kiri jalan warung-warung makanan juga pada rame diserbu pendaki2 yang lagi nyari sarapan. Jam 7an, kita udah nyampe di kaki gunung sekaligus tempat parkir. Gue gak abis pikir dapet penampakan kaki gunung segitu rame! Rame gila! Dari bayi sampe lansia gue ketemu. Beda banget kaya di Gn. Talang kemaren, sepi. Nyampe parkiran kita langsung nyari orang yang jualan bubur ayam. Ketemu. Kita langsung sarapan disana. Abis makan, gue sama #1 pergi beli sarung tangan sama baf yang gak jauh dari sana. Tiba-tiba gue mules (oke, ini gak pantes diceritain di catper). Celingak-celinguk orientasi medan buat nemuin toilet. Kurang lebih 2 menit, toilet umum pun ketemu. #1 #3 pada nungguin gue. Setelah itu, kita pamit ke ortu yang bakal nungguin di bawah nantinya. Ortu gue emang terkenal dgn ke-parnoannya dikalangan temen2 gue #1 dan #3. Sebelum kita naik, ortu kembali nanyain kesiapan kita dll untuk yang udah kesekian-puluh-kalinya-kalo-diitung-dari-Bintaro. â€œTerlalu perhatiannya orang tua merupakan gangguan terindah yang kelak akan disadari anak-anaknyaâ€ â€“Raditya Dika Jam 7 lewat kita bikin lingkaran buat berdoa. Pendakian pun dimulai. Trek awal makdam, batu2an. Kita banyak ketemu sama pendaki yang turun maupun yang sama-sama naik. Disini gue sadar betapa hangat dan ramahnya manusia waktu di gunung. Kita saling sapa, nanyain darimana, nawarin makanan dll padahal belum kenal dan belum pernah ketemu sebelumnya. Gak ada kata tengsin. Padahal mah kalo ketemu di mall atau tempat lain kan gak ada yang sapa-sapaan kayak gini. Asap-asap belerang udah mulai keliatan dan tercium. Gue buru-buru narik baf ke hidung yang daritadi cuma gue kalungin di leher. Kita udah sampai di Kawah Papandayan. Asap belerang dimana-mana. #3 mulai ngeluh macem-macem. #3 Gue dan #1 Lanjut jalan, kita berenti bentar deket warung. Break, gue beli gorengan 5 potong di warung karna gak ada kembalian. Setelah break, kita lanjut jalan menuju Pondok Saladah. Di jalan menuju Pondok Saladah kita sering break buat foto-foto. Orang ganteng Lagi ketawa, gigi kering saking dinginnya Selfie kita Trek menuju Pondok Saladah lumayan becek dan menguras tenaga buat nge-rem sebelum jatoh indah. Almond Milk. 8 Tbs pure White Almond Butter 4 Tbs vegan Rice Syrup (optional) 3 2/5 cups (800 ml) lukewarm water Mix almond butter and rice syrup in a beaker. Slowly add lukewarm water while stirring fast and thoroughly. (It is easiest to use a blender.) Store in the fridge. The rice syrup is optional, but this amount does not really sweeten the almond milk. It tops off the taste and is highly recommended. To prevent the almond milk from curdling in your coffee, add a generous pinch of baking soda to the coffee beforehand. If you do not like almonds or if you want a little variety, try making cashew milk, hazelnut milk, or even macadamia milk. Any kind of pure white nut butter should work. If you are allergic to nuts, you can use pure white tiger nut butter. Tiger nuts are suitable for people with nut allergies.

preprotext: Journal 5.23. When I got up today, I talked to Matt for two and a half hours. It was so nice to be able to talk on my own phone in my own bed. I told him everything from the past few days and he told me about his. It was really nice. I love talking with him. It makes me feel so calm about where I am excited for the future. After the housekeeper asked me a few times if I was going to be ready soon (as I was in bed in pajamas at noon) I finally got up to shower and get ready. I didnâ€™t realize how much I missed taking a shower with hot water that came from the wall. It was magical. Putting on makeup also felt so good. Itâ€™s vain, I know, but it makes me feel like a real person out in the world rather than someone who is just passing through or roughing it for the time being. It made me feel like, â€œThis is my life, I am here to stay and Iâ€™m prepared for it.â€ When I left, it was around 2 pm and I went to the main mall which is a few blocks from my house. I kind of wandered around for a while before finding a grocery store. Note: grocery stores donâ€™t sell razors. I still need to find one. I did buy; however, a kg of tomatoes, coconut oil, a body sponge, shower gel, broccoli, two sweet potatoes, two instant soups, a kg of carrots, a big cucumber, an onion, and salt for about 13 us dollars though! Food is going to be so cheap here, Iâ€™m so excited. And Iâ€™m going to eat really well! I bought way more than I had expected so my bag was too heavy to keep walking around with and I decided to go home. When I was walking back a man yelled to me asking if I had anything good for him and his friend in the bag. I said â€œjust vegetablesâ€ and he came up to me and asked me if I was a vegetarian. I explained what a vegan was and he asked how long I had been not eating meat for and if I ever craved it. His name is Richard and we ended up talking to him and his friends for about an hour and a half. He explained to me how Americans often suck when they travel to Africa and donâ€™t take the time to make real friends, so he hopes that I am not like that. He runs a supply chain for souvenir-type items, so he had to give money and an order to one of the women with us because she was heading to Joburg the next day to pick things up to then distribute. One girl, a 23 year old named Wame, asked me to go to her birthday party coming up. I of course said yes and we exchanged numbers for whatsapp. All the women immediately asked me to get them white boyfriendsâ€¦ Race is really interesting here. When I told the housekeeper about this she asked if Richard was white or black. But he was really nice and offered me travel tips for safaris and stuff! When I was finally walking out a younger man (Richard was in his forties with a 9 year old son) stopped me and introduced himself. He told me like 6 times that I was beautiful before saying anything else. He then asked where I was staying and if he could come over. He also asked if I would like to get to know him more while I am here. When I said no to him coming over and that I had a boyfriend so I would like to just be friends, he asked me to give him my name for Facebook and that he wants to hang out tomorrowâ€¦ I wonâ€™t hang out with him. He seemed a bit deterred by me saying that I didnâ€™t want to sleep with him, but did say â€œIâ€™m single but that doesnâ€™t mean Iâ€™m not looking for anything.â€ He then started talking about how he needs to get me to stay in the country so we should get married. I think that it was mostly just cultural differences and I didnâ€™t feel threatened at all by him, it was just a really interesting look into the culture of dating. All of this made me very aware of my place in this city as a white girl. I donâ€™t know if they see me as akin to colonizers, an idiot with a lot of money, an object to get American citizenship, or just simply someone with whom they can have cultural exchange and practice English. I am amazed by how good the English of everyone here is! Itâ€™s very refreshing in comparison to the way that people in Rwanda speak English. I should thank the British for colonizing this area I suppose. The French in Rwanda was much better than the English, and here English is amazing. The grammar is all correct and although everyone has accents, they are very slight. Iâ€™m really excited for the next two months in this country. When I got home, I watched some AHS and Parks and Rec while I ate my instant noodle soup and sliced cucumbers and tomatoes with salt and balsamic vinegar. It was a really good dinner!ï¿½ï¿½ I blogged a bit and worked on figuring out where I should check out in the city, but the internet was in and out all night, so it was difficult to have enough time to really do much. Iâ€™m going to the Orange store tomorrow to buy a dongle so I can always have internet. I also talked to Nick a bit about his life and how I feel like this is a glimpse at real like and the need to reach out to stay in touch with friends, because you wonâ€™t just run into people when youâ€™re halfway around the world from them. Being out here feels strangely isolating. For one, I have been in my own apartment essentially for two days â€“ so for the most part I am really alone. But because of lack of internet, I feel like the lives of my American friends are going on while Iâ€™m over here in this little bubble. Thatâ€™s disheartening because I want to explode the bubble to tap into the people of Botswana and other parts of Africa, but there are so many institutional and logistical barriers to that. Maybe I will start a company that will aim at flattening the world and reaching into Africaâ€¦

The Islamic State group has launched attacks on multiple fronts in Iraqâ€™s western province of Anbar, in its latest attempt to retake the initiative on the ground, sources on both sides said. An assault launched late Thursday left the governmentâ€™s claim to Ramadi hanging by a thread again, with IS fighters advancing to within metres (yards) of the provincial headquarters. â€œThe situation is critical in the Ramadi battle following an attack by Daesh terrorists last night,â€ provincial council member Adhal Obeid al-Fahdawi said, using an Arab acronym for IS. â€œPolice, army forces and tribal forces are defending the city as we speak to prevent IS from taking over entirely. Iraqi and coalition aircraft are in support,â€ he said. preprotext: On this day two years ago, I met Abba for the first time, a thin, weary, nameless mare pulled out of a stable in the back of the bush. She had been kept there for at least a year, possibly two. Rats had eaten her tail down to the dock and chewed the back of her heels. Her mane was falling out in clumps. She was wormy, half-starved and thinner than she looked beneath a fluffy dull coat that was covered in bot fly eggs. There were bald patches and scarring the length of her back from the oversized, ill-fitting saddle she was ridden in, and a damaged muscle in her left haunch from being galloped flat out on the beach without any warm up or cool down. But despite all this there was a spark in her eye and a zest for life. I was just there to take pictures of her but as I watched her walking around the field in her new home, I had to admit that she was kind of cute. Seven months later she was mine. Happy eighth birthday, Abba pony. I may never know your real birth date, or what happened to you in the first six years of your life, but I promise that I will never allow you to be starved and ill-treated again. You may be spoiled rotten these days, eating only the best apples, flirting with your many paramours, and having the run of massive fields full of the most fattening grass, but you deserve it, you opinionated little pony mare. You bring joy to everyone who meets you and put smiles on their faces even on awful days. Sweet girl, youâ€™re a spirit of sunshine in my life and you mean the world to me. Love you, Abracadabra.

I watched Before Midnight today and it was a really great movie. It was interesting to see Jesse and Celine interacting with other characters in the first half an hour of the movie then they went off by themselves on their walk to the hotel and it was beautiful to watch again. I like when they have random conversations about anything and everything. They seemed so in love the first half of the movie until they had that horrible argument at the hotel room about moving to Chicago to be with his son and her not wanting to because she didnâ€™t want to give up on her dreams. I get not wanting to give up on dreams but she came off a bit selfish tbh and people on IMDb when I looked at one thread said the same. They did sort of feel like different people at that point. They were so in love and obviously got together after he stayed in Paris to be with her even though he was still married and then they got together and had 2 daughters but didnâ€™t marry. But the argument was so hateful and yes people argue, thatâ€™s true to life but saying the stuff they did seemed a bit out of character. But then she said she didnâ€™t love him any more but he went and found her, pretending to meet her for the first time and I think they may have just shrugged it off and stayed together in the end. I hope so because I really liked Jesse and Celine together and am glad they did finally get together and have kids. Ethan Hawke and Julie Delpy were again superb as their respective characters though, a real joy to watch. You do find them very believable as a couple. I wish I had something like that with someone minus the crazy arguments lol. I hope they make another movie to show them further down the line and hopefully still happy and as romantic as Before Sunrise which I think is still my favourite one.ï¿½ï¿½ Ethan Hawke as Jesse <3

The lyrics often make no sense, if they are in any recognised language at all, like â€œDiggi-Loo Diggi-Leyâ€ by golden-booted Swedish Mormon brothers Herreys in 1984, â€œLa La Laâ€ in 1968 or Luluâ€™s â€œBoom-Bang-A-Bangâ€ in 1969. Horseshoe Casino Cleveland, on its third anniversary, cites impact in Cleveland. CLEVELAND, Ohio - Three years after opening its doors on Public Square, Horseshoe Casino Cleveland is touting the millions it has paid in jackpots, taxes and sponsorships. The casino also has drawn millions of people to the city, resulting in tens of thousands of hotel rooms being booked and thousands of free meals being served to high rollers. While the casino has provided jobs and paid taxes, revenues have been stagnant and no future expansion plans have been presented. Annual revenue, according to the Ohio Casino Control Commission, was $176.4 million from May-December 2012, $242.6 million in 2013 and $220.4 million in 2014. Monthly revenue exceeded $20 million each month in 2012, with the all-time high of $26.1 million in June, 2012. The casino exceeded $20 million a month in revenue five times in 2013, twice in 2014 and once thus far this year. The casino sent a press release that included the following information on its impact since opening on May 14, 2012. 13.2 million: guest visits 99,000: hotel rooms booked $4.4 million: comped meals in local restaurants $181.3 million: jackpots paid 1,730: jobs created (90 percent from Cleveland area) $147.7 million: payroll $14.8 million: payroll taxes $4.5 million: sponsorships $3.5 million: charitable donations $7.4 million: taxes through March paid to Cuyahoga County $11.4 million: taxes through March paid to Cleveland $48.7 million: taxes through March paid to schools in seven counties

KUALA LUMPUR, May 26 â€” 1Malaysia Development Berhad (1MDB) can overcome its financial problems, but the indebted firm is being hampered by negative media coverage and criticism, a minister has said. Fears that public funds may be used to â€œbail outâ€ the state-owned firm that reportedly accumulated RM42 billion in debt in just over five years has prompted opposition towards its transactions, both old and new. A recent sale of land in the Tun Razak Exchange to Lembaga Tabung Haji triggered public uproar, forcing the Muslim pilgrims fund to immediately seek to dispose of the property a little over a month after the purchase. The controversy surrounding 1MDB has also spooked a consortium of German banks to consider rescinding a US$975 million (RM3.523 billion) loan ahead of its August maturity, putting 1MDB at risk of a cross-default of the entirety of its RM42 billion in liabilities. Congolese expert Jean-Jacques Muyembe may be little known to the public, but he has been one of the worldâ€™s top Ebola investigators since the first epidemic erupted in central Africa in 1976. Now, amid a decline in a west African outbreak that has taken more than 11,000 lives, Muyembe warns that Ebola will strike again in the future and that the deadly virus poses â€œa threat to the whole worldâ€. Muyembe studied medicine in Kinshasa and at the University of Leuven in Belgium. He returned home to the Democratic Republic of Congo â€“ then known as Zaire â€“ in 1976, when the northern village of Yambuku was struck by a mysterious disease. â€œThey said many people were dying, and the health ministry asked me to go investigate,â€ Muyembe told AFP. He initially thought it could be a case of typhoid fever but he decided to continue investigating until he got to the bottom of it. â€œI drew blood, and had no protective gloves or clothing,â€ Muyembe said. Accompanied by a Belgian nun suffering from fever, he returned from Yambuku to Kinshasa. It was her blood samples, shipped in a makeshift cooler to the Institute of Tropical Medicine in Antwerp, that enabled scientist Peter Piot to identify the worm-looking virus for the first time. It was then named after the Ebola river, located near the area first hit by the epidemic. â€œThen there was total silence until 1995,â€ Muyembe said. That year, he was summoned to Tikwit in the south of DR Congo where a bloody diarrhoea outbreak was decimating the population, including medical staff. â€œI examined an Italian nun and saw signs that reminded me of the Yambuku incident,â€ Muyembe said. He discovered that contamination â€œhad taken place in the operation room â€“ in other words, from the patientâ€™s bloodâ€. Muyembeâ€™s discovery that the virus is transmitted through bodily fluids was a key find. â€œFrom then on, we put in place strategies to fight against the disease, isolating patients, following up on people they had been in contact with, and mobilising communities,â€ he said. â€œThese are strategies that the World Health Organization practises today.â€ Professor Muyembeâ€™s team then started testing serotherapy on patients. â€œWe drew blood from people recovering from Ebola, and injected it into eight sick patients. Seven of them survived, even though there was an 80 percent mortality rate,â€ he said. This type of treatment is now being studied for its potential. - â€˜Ebola can strike anywhereâ€™ - Even after decades fighting the deadly virus, Muyembe said he was â€œsurprisedâ€ by the sheer size of the resurgence in Guinea in late 2013. â€œWe thought Ebola epidemics could be brought under control quickly,â€ he said. Previously, DR Congo had successfully put an end to seven epidemics. â€œThese countries (in west Africa) believed that Ebola was a central and eastern African problem. They werenâ€™t prepared,â€ he added. The epidemic has now ended in Liberia, and is declining in Sierra Leone. But in Guinea, â€œnew cases continue to appearâ€, Muyembe said. â€œWe need to find the most recent cases, even if they are hidden deep in the forest, because if the disease becomes endemic, it would be terrible for the whole world,â€ he warned. â€œIn 10 or 20 yearsâ€™ time, this epidemic will return, and we need to be prepared,â€ he said. â€œEbola can strike anywhere, and we need to be vigilant. Muyembe also sees the prize as a way to encourage young Africans studying abroad to return to work. â€œI have made my career in DR Congo, despite all the conflicts my country has known,â€ the researcher said. â€œWe must build up labs and research centres in Africa,â€ he added, â€œso that when the danger arrives, we can stop it in time. This is the lesson we must learn from this epidemic.â€

preprotext: So Long, Columbia House. And Thanks for Making Me Cool Itâ€™s easy toÂ romanticize the days of physical media. Iâ€™m just old enough to remember the thrill of tracking down a hard-to-find album in a used CD bin and the pleasure of owning something special. I remember how long a new album seemed to last before it felt â€œstale.â€ I remember sitting down to listen to a new CDâ€”really listen to it, not just play it in the background while I juggled 30 other things. I remember all this, and sure, I miss it sometimes. But thereâ€™s no way I would go back. Because in all honesty, the days of music scarcity sucked. As a teenager living in rural Wyoming, the sort of music I wanted to listen to was hard to come by. And even with a generous allowance, at $15 to $20 a pop, building a CD collection was expensive. Without any way to preview an album before plunking down cash, each CD was a risky investment. I became cool overnight, at least in my own head, and practically for free. Thatâ€™s why Columbia Houseâ€”whose parent company said this week it was filing for bankruptcyâ€”was so amazing. For those who donâ€™t remember, Columbia House was basically a subscription service that gave you 10 CDs or tapes for just one cent when you signed up. In exchange, you agreed to buy a set number of albums at full price over the next year. What this meant in practice: one day I had, like, two bootlegged cassettes in my collection. The next day I had a 10-album collection that included Nine Inch Nails, Nirvana, Machines of Loving Grace, and The Cure. I became cool overnight, at least in my own head, and practically for free. That may sound superficial, but getting to sample so many different bands was practically unheard of, short of buying one of those compilation CDs full of pop hits. Even if I wasnâ€™t as cool as the kids in big cities who could find records from indie labels, I was able to find albums by bands like Joy Division, Skinny Puppy, and Ministryâ€”stuff Iâ€™d never have been able to buy at the local Walmart. That was 1995, making me part of the last generation to experience the service before the post-scarcity era of online music. Today my young rural counterparts have smart phones that can stream millions of songs for free, provided theyâ€™re willing to sit through a few ads. Sites like Bandcamp and Soundcloud provide an entire galaxy of obscure indie music to which only people reading the hippest `zines of the old era would ever have been privy. Those kids will never know the joy of opening that first 10-CD bundle, that feeling of being transformed from nerd to hipster in the blink of an eye. But theyâ€™ll also never spend $20 plus shipping and handling to find out an album sucks. That sounds like a fair trade to me. Although we were shocked to hear that the one time giant Columbia House still existed, it is with a small tear that weÂ bid adieu to the company that helped the GREAT Hootie & The Blowfish sell three million extra copies of Cracked Rear View. Ride on Hootie, ride on into the night. You too Columbia records, you tooâ€¦ Â

Is Nessie Really an Otter!?!?. From its tail to its characteristic hump and smooth, dinosaur-like head, it looks every inch like Scotlandâ€™s favorite monster. But one expert claims this photo is proof that Nessie is probably a much smaller and more common creature. On close inspection, the three â€˜humpsâ€™ are revealed to be the head, back and tail of an otter. The image was taken by Dr Jonathan Wills, off Lerwick in Shetland, and is of a female otter known locally as Dratsie. Her head, back and tail form three very distinctive humps which, at a distance could be mistaken for a much larger creature. Dr Wills says the image taken this week proves the beast said to prowl the depths of Loch Ness, hundreds of miles away, is more likely a 4ft otter than a monster.

To add to the uncertainty, the position that should have Theo Walcottâ€™s name on it has been a revolving door this season, due in part to Walcottâ€™s fitness and unconvincing form earlier in the season, and part because of the lung-busting commitment of Danny Welbeck, whoâ€“while very usefulâ€“seems allergic to scoring. The wages and values numbers for Arsenalâ€™s forward position group are below: Based on the numbers from the originalï¿½ï¿½Value for moneyï¿½ï¿½post from a few days ago (and seen below), the 10 forwards on Arsenalâ€™s currently on books make up a significant (nearly 30%) portion of the total wage bill, pulling a total of 2.92% per player. This is the second-highest paid position group per player. A problem becomes evident when one takes into account the last column of the table above. The total percent of value (based on the numbers from transfermarkt.com) the team derives from its forward line players is vastly outweighed by the investment into them. preprotext: Goins, Encarnacion hit long ball to lead Blue Jays over Mariners 8-2. TORONTO - Ryan Goins and Edwin Encarnacion hit two-run homers and Aaron Sanchez had a second straight solid pitching performance as the Toronto Blue Jays pounded the Seattle Mariners 8-2 on Sunday. Goins, with his first home run of the season, and Encarnacion, with his eighth of the month, both homered in the fifth inning to give Sanchez (4-4) all the support he needed at Rogers Centre. The young right-hander, making just the ninth start of his Major League career, followed up his 7-1/3 inning performance on Tuesday with 6-2/3 on Sunday as Toronto salvaged a win in the final game of a three-game series against the Mariners. The Blue Jays (20-26) are just 3-8 over the past 11 games. Kyle Seager hit a solo shot for the Mariners (20-23). Seattle right-hander Taijuan Walker (1-5) held the Blue Jays hitless through the first four innings. But Toronto jumped all over him in the fifth, sending eight men to the plate and scoring four times. Kevin Pillar, who came into Sunday batting just .121 over his previous 16 games, started things by flaring a lead-off single down the right-field line. Goins brought him home by pounding a fastball from Walker off the back wall of the Mariners bullpen for his first homer of the season and fourth of his career. After Russell Martin doubled with two out, Encarnacion drilled a 3-2 fastball from Walker into the second deck over the left centre-field fence for his team-leading 12th home run of the season to make it 4-1. Seattle cut the Toronto lead to two runs in the top of the seventh before the Blue Jays ended the drama by scoring four more runs in the bottom of the inning to make it 8-2. Jose Bautista sat out Sundayâ€™s game after receiving a cortisone shot in his right shoulder. Bautista has been nursing a sore shoulder and not playing in the outfield since injuring it in a game on April 21. Seager opened the scoring in the second by hammering a Sanchez curveball into the seats beyond the right centre-field wall for his seventh homer of the season. After surrendering that home run, the 22-year-old Sanchez settled into a rhythm, striking out four and walking a pair while allowing seven hits in a 95-pitch performance. Roberto Osuna, Aaron Loup and Liam Hendriks combined to throw 2-1/3 innings of scoreless relief. The Blue Jays continue their 10-game homestand Monday, opening a three-games series against the Chicago White Sox.

preprotext: The Jackets of Resort 2016. Every element of clothing has a significant meaning. Talking about first impressions, the jacket is what veils the outfit underneath and itâ€™s what most people first notice about somebody. Especially if one is standing in a distance from the observer. With every season the function of the jacket is gracefully transitioning, and the most recognized designers make sure to keep the sparkles on the runways burning, introducing us to pieces that rise eyelids and temperatures. Take a look! At Louis Vuitton there is such a strong space statement, that it looks like Gisele Pletzer just came back from Tomorrowland, carrying wondrous treasures in her suitcase. The collar of the jacket is so magnificent, that itâ€™s making the prospects of any neckline-accesorising look futile. Love it!ï¿½ï¿½ There is something solid and yet ethereal about Bottega Venetaâ€™s signature jacket of the Resort 2016 collection. It obviously has its own story to tell and itâ€™s a story of a beautiful blend.. As if itâ€™s an idea, an object, that is being materialized right at this moment. If an asymmetry can look in harmony, Iâ€™m sure thatâ€™s what it looks like. It was a challenging task to choose which jacket from Chanel to discuss in my post. Not only because the word jacket is automatically associated with the Fashion House, but because Karl Lagerfeld is a fashion virtuoso whose work is a diamond bond of quality and quantity. As a result, the Resort 2016 collection in Seoul is a spring of beautiful garments that make a lasting impression. The reason I chose this one in particular is the fact that on a background made of tweed, itâ€™s surprisingly lovely of Chanel to present us with an almost-sporty looking wind jacket in such a vibrant color. With the whole flawless styling, it gives a sense of youth and neo pop. Viva Chanel StreetCouture! Raf Simons seems to have given Dior a load of New Age attitude. Stripes, mesh, a fraction of a beeâ€™s sweetness interpreted in small shapes, and a graceful neckline. Altogether? Why not. To describe the result in one word, I would say: Effervescent.
